message.content: The paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. Other likely sub-categories could include "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to the topic of question generation. "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be possible sub-categories as they involve techniques used in the paper such as attention mechanisms and sequence to sequence models.
